HEADWORD: Borofluoride
<hw>Bo`ro*flu"or*ide</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Boron</ets> + <ets>fluoride</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A double fluoride of boron and hydrogen, or some other positive
element, or radical; -- called also <altname>fluoboride</altname>, and
formerly <altname>fluoborate</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

